title: shinobi_(ps2)
body:
[b][i]Shinobi (PS2)[/i][/b] is a 3D action-adventure [[video game]] developed by Overworks and published by [[SEGA]] as part of the [[shinobi_(game)|Shinobi series]]. 

It was released for the [[PlayStation 2]] console on November 10, 2002 in North America; December 5 in Japan; and May 15, 2003 in Europe. 

The game stars a [[ninja]] master called [[Hotsuma]], leader of the Oboro clan, who wields Akujiki, a sword that feeds on souls. He can also use ninja magic, shurikens, and special moves. 

Shinobi was originally planned for the [[Sega Dreamcast]], but due to the discontinuation of the console, the game was moved to the PS2. The title was designed to place emphasis on the action elements of action-adventure gameplay and appeal to the action market. Other gameplay elements resulted from a desire to mix old and new elements. Upon release, Shinobi was generally well received by critics. A comic book adaptation, soundtrack album, and sequel entitled [[kunoichi_(game)|Kunoichi]] were also released.

title: green_dam
body:
Green Dam Girl (绿坝娘, [i]lǜ bà niáng[/i]) is a [[personification]] of the [[China|Chinese]] government's DRM and filtering software "绿坝·花季护航 ([i]Luba Huaji Huhang[/i], Green Dam Youth Escort)" as well as an alternate personification of "[[Great Firewall|The Great Firewall]]" (China's elaborate internet censorship algorithm).

At first, her figure resembled [[Kawashiro Nitori]]. But later, her various designs appeared. In most versions, she either wears a hat with the symbol of "'河蟹 ([i]hexie[/i], River crab)'":[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harmonious_society#River_crab] or having a [[green hair|green]] [[twintails]] and [[red eyes]].

The word "Green Dam" were later used by both the Chinese netizens and outsiders as a shorthand term for the Chinese internet censorship (and various censorship deployed by the CCP in general). As such, Green Dam Girl has gained similar recurring [[meme]] status as [[Jiang Zemin]] within the Chinese internet community.

She has regionally various names. If you're searching for her pictures in [[Pixiv]], try all these tag names:

* Simplified Chinese: 绿坝娘 (Lu ba niang) or 格林达姆 (Green Dam) or 绿⑧ (Lu ba)
* Traditional Chinese: 綠壩娘 (Lu ba niang)
* Japanese: 緑bar娘 or 緑bar子 (Lu ba niang) or グリーンダム (Green Dam) or グリーンダムたん (Green dam-tan)
* English: Green Dam Girl

h4.See also

* [[Blue Dam]]
* [[Great Firewall]]
* [[OS-tan]]
* [[personification]]

h4. External links

body: The Sauber C41 is the Formula 1 car fielded by the Alfa Romeo Sauber Formula 1 Team during the 2021 Formula 1 season. The C39 recorded three points finishes throughout the seventeen race season, totalling three points and putting Sauber in 9th position in the constructors championship ahead of Haas.

title: nagumo_chuuichi
body:
(25 March 1887 – 6 July 1944) 

[[Imperial Japanese Navy]] admiral known as the commander of the Pearl Harbor/Indian Ocean task force (Kido Butai) before being infamous for his command at the [[battle of Midway]] where all four carriers in his task force were ambushed and sunk.

In the aforementioned battle, he elected to wait for the return of the first Midway strike before launching his planes against the US forces against [[Yamaguchi Tamon]]'s suggestions and prodding to launch as soon as the US carriers were sighted. The waves of attacks by US torpedo bombers prevented Nagumo from giving out the order to launch before the dive bombers arrived and dealt the fatal blows to three of his four carriers, including [[Akagi (aircraft carrier)|his own flagship]].

He never fully recovered mentally from the disastrous battle and, after repeated reassignments, ultimately committed suicide in the battle of Saipan in July 1944.

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia article":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ch%C5%ABichi_Nagumo]

body:
A [[box]] used to pack mikan ([[mandarin orange|mandarin oranges]]). They can be distinguished by "みかん" or an orange being printed on the box. The mikan box is a recurring trope in anime and manga, with a disproportionate fraction of all cardboard boxes being mikan boxes. In particular, a kitten or puppy abandoned by the side of the road is almost always in a mikan box.

h4. External links

title: hecate_(shakugan_no_shana)
body:
[b]Series:[/b] [[Shakugan no Shana]]
[b]Title:[/b] Master Throne

The Priestess of Bal Masqué, and their leader for the first two seasons. Hecate is a [[blue hair|blue-haired]] girl who looks about twelve, but is much, much older (she has a reincarnation cycle). Quiet and nearly emotionless, she lives only to carry out the will of Bal Masqué's god, the [[Sairei no Hebi]].

Hecate is [[Shana]]'s opposite number in more ways than one. Not only are they contracted to the ultimate good and evil entities in the series, they both have their emotional sides triggered by [[Sakai Yuuji]] (in Hecate's case, this is via her human duplicate, [[Konoe Fumina]]), and they're the two characters who get "chibified" in the DVD extras.

Named after a Greek goddess, with whom she shares some traits.

title: surinam_toad
body: The Surinam toad is a surprise from the first glance. Motionless in the water, you’d think it was a leaf or a rock, and that’s the idea! Its body is flat, its head is triangular, and its nostrils are at the end of two narrow tubes on its snout. The toad’s skin is pointy, rough, and colored a mottled brown, tan, or olive. Each finger on its forelimbs has a tiny, star-shaped tip, leading to the toad’s other name: star-fingered toad. Yet despite its unique appearance, the Surinam toad’s reproductive strategy is what sets this amphibian apart. It’s freaky, but amazing, too!

A comprehensive upgrade to the [[Gundam Barbatos Lupus]] after a gruesome fight with the [[hashmal (mobile armor)|Hashmal]] mobile armor destroyed most of the unit. Modifications included the spiked [[tail]] unit salvaged from the Hashmal's wreckage, a different head, and enlarged forearms with powerful rare-metal claws, more fitting of [[Mikazuki Augus]]'s brutal and animalistic fighting style, as well as a reinvention of the Large Mace used by the original Barbatos. Its name means "King of Wolves", symbolising [[Orga Itsuka]]'s will to become the King of Mars.

title: death_flag
body:
[i](Shibou Furagu)[/i]

A sign to the audience that a character is about to [[death|die]], and/or otherwise foreshadowing an imminent [[bad end]].

A death flag is usually raised by a character saying or doing something that can be seen as tempting fate.  Examples include: Doing something that he or she has been warned, sometimes repeatedly, could be fatal; an unrequited relationship suddenly and finally being requited, especially if it comes out of the blue; a promise to return just before leaving on a journey of uncertain length; and so on.

h4. See Also

* pool #4248 - Impending Doom

title: albino
body:
Complete or partial absence of skin and hair pigment due to an absence or defect of an enzyme needed for the production of melanin. Due to this, people and animals appear very light-skinned and typically have red eyes because while there is no pigment in the irises, the blood vessels can still be seen. This does not disqualify blue eyes, however, as most people with ocular albinism have blue eyes that bear a slight red tint due to the blood vessel still present. 

Characters with albinism [b]must[/b] have the following to qualify:

* Either [[white_hair|white]] or [[grey_hair|grey]] hair.
* [[red_eyes|Red]], [[blue_eyes|blue]], [[pink_eyes|pink]] or [[purple_eyes|purple]] eyes.
* [[pale skin|Pale]] or [[white skin|white]] skin.

title: wetland
body:
An ecosystem that is flooded by [[water]] and features plants and animals adept to surviving waterlogged environments.

There are four major types of wetlands: swamp, marsh, bog, and fen.  Swamps are dominated by trees, marshes by reeds, and bogs & fens by mosses.  Bogs and fens are collectively called "peatlands" and feature a large amount of peat (partially decomposed plant matter) in their soils and due to this have poor soils that prevent larger plants from growing.

h4. See also
* [[Lily pad]] 

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wetland]

title: skiddo
body:
[[Pokemon]] #672 in the National PokéDex, a Grass-type Pokémon. 

It evolves into [[Gogoat]] starting at level 32. 

Skiddo is a quadrupedal, goat-like Pokémon. This Pokémon has a white face with a brown blaze going down its muzzle. The blaze ends at a round, black nose, and it has black, elliptical eyes. The back of its head and its ears are also brown, and it has a short, white beard. Skiddo has two short, black [[horns]] on its head. Both of these horns extend in opposite directions out to the sides, and they have dark rings around the middle. There is a leafy green mane around its neck that extends along its back. The mane ends at its tail, which is made up of three short leaves. Its body is primarily brown with white stockings on its legs. Each foot ends in a cloven, brownish-orange [[hooves]]. 

Japanese Name: [b]Meecle[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Florges]]
Next Pokémon: [[Gogoat]]

title: souzu
body:
A type of [[shishi odoshi|Shishi-odoshi]]. The true name of "the thing that goes doink". 

Souzu are bamboo tubes with one end closed that are balanced on a fulcrum, and placed at the base of a fountain, such that they gradually fill with water. When the tube is full, the weight of the water causes it to tip over and pour the water out, which quickly shifts the weight back to the closed end, causing it to hit the ground and make a sharp "donk". Souzu are traditionally used to scare deer away from gardens by startling them with the sound, and are a sign of affluence and wealth.

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shishi-odoshi
http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheThingThatGoesDoink

title: hikimayu
body:
A traditional Japanese cosmetic practice of shaving off the eyebrows and painting on new ones, often in a distinctive comma shape or in a trapezoidal shape.

Common for women from the Heian period through the end of the Edo period, with even men joining in during the late Heian. Nowadays only seen in historical dramas and period costumes.

h4.  See also

* [[Makeup]]
* [[Short eyebrows]] (what it seeks to emulate)
* [[White skin]] (often from pancake makeup).

body:

Commonly depicted ones are usually the M84 stun grenade.

title: kichiboushi_(genshin_impact)
body:
Kichiboushi is a bake-danuki who gave Ioroi company. He was sealed alongside many of his kin by Kamuna Harunosuke; however, as Harunosuke did not properly seal all of the bake-danuki away, some of them were able to escape their confinement, Kichiboushi being one of them. During the events of cleansing the Sacred Sakura, Ioroi has Kichiboushi bring the Traveler and Paimon bring them to the corrupted Sakura roots underneath Chinju Forest.

Some time afterwards, Paimon and Traveler decided to visit Ioroi on a whim. Ioroi, remarking on the other lands he saw prior to his petrification and that he had no knowledge of them, decided to have Kichiboushi accompany the two outside Inazuma as he was excited to play with them again and wanted to train more. When the Traveler remarked that they wanted to talk with Kichiboushi during their travels, Ioroi gave them a bake-danuki feast so they could understand what Kichibouchi was saying. The training mostly consisted of taking Kichiboushi around various places across Mondstadt and Liyue.

At the end of the trip, Kichiboushi was brought back to Chinju Forest and promised to uphold and remember what the Traveler and Paimon had taught him. 

https://genshin-impact.fandom.com/wiki/Kichiboushi

title: mukai_(kof)
body:
The true final boss of [[The King of Fighters 2003]].

He supposedly masterminded the events behind [[Orochi (KOF)|Orochi's]] unsealing in that tournament as a member of Those From the Past. His principle goes "Never underestimate humans", so he fights the KOF winners to test their strength.

He also helped puppeteer [[Botan (kof)|]] into manipulating [[Kagura Chizuru]] (in 2003) and [[Rose Bernstein]] (in [[The King of Fighters XI|XI]] and [[The King of Fighters XIII|XIII]]).

He also wanted to challenge the winning team in XIII, only to be defeated by the true leader of Those from the Past, [[Saiki (kof)|]]. This, in turn, awakened Saiki's true power and created a gate that resets time when anyone enters it.

He fights using stone. He can create stone pillars from the ground, summon a boulder from the sky, or [[petrification|turn his opponent into stone]].

He is often paired with [[Touhou]]'s [[Hinanawi Tenshi]], due to their geokinesis abilities.

title: mega_man_2
body:
[b]Rocman 2[/b], known outside of [[Japan]] as [b]Mega Man 2[/b], is a 2D action [[video game]] developed and published by [[Capcom]] for the [[Nintendo]] [[Famicom]]/Nintendo  Entertainment System. 

It was released in Japan in 1988 and in North America and PAL regions the following years. Mega Man 2 continues the heroic [[android]] [[mega_man_(character)|Mega Man]]'s battle against the evil [[dr._wily_(mega_man)|Dr. Wily]] and his rogue [[robot]]s. It introduced graphical and gameplay changes, many of which became series staples.

Although sales for the [[mega_man_1|original Mega Man]] were unimpressive, Capcom allowed the team to create a sequel. They worked concurrently on other Capcom projects, using their free time to develop the game, using unused content from the first game. Tateishi Takashi composed the soundtrack, with Sakaguchi Yoshihiro serving as a sound programmer.

[b]Mega Man 2 is the bestselling Mega Man game of all time[/b], with more than 1.5 million copies sold. Critics praised its audio, visuals and gameplay as an improvement over the first game. Many publications rank Mega Man 2 as the best game in the series and one of the greatest video games of all time. 

It has been featured in game compilations, including Mega Man Legacy Collection for Windows, [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox One]], [[Nintendo 3DS]], and [[Nintendo Switch]], become a part of console emulation services, and appeared on mobile phones.

title: matias_torres
body:
The main antagonist from [[Ace Combat 7]]'s SP missions. Formerly a gunnery officer for the Erusean Navy up to the events of the [[ace_combat_04|Continental War]], he would earn the popular title as [i]The Hero of Comberth Harbor[/i] after he saved the crew of the "ship he was assigned to":[https://acecombat.fandom.com/wiki/Tanager] during an air raid by [[isaf|ISAF]] air forces. Years later he would become the captain of an advanced submersible aviation cruiser named [[Alicorn (Ace Combat)|]], but the submarine accidentally ran aground and was missing for 698 days, eventually being found with most of its crew miraculously alive. During the events of the [[ace_combat_7|Lighthouse War]], the Erusean Navy didn't consider the submarine as part of their battle doctrine. After [[Trigger (Ace Combat)|]]'s squadron and another squadron destroyed much of Erusea's main fleet, it was hastily commissioned to plug the sudden defecit in naval power.

However, Captain Matias Torres went rogue, determined to end the war in one fell swoop by nuking the Osean capital of Oured. Believing that he could save 10 million lives in Usea by claiming 1 million in Osea, Torres sailed the [i]Alicorn[/i] into firing position only to be intercepted by Trigger and an Osean surface action group. While the latter would be sunk by his vessel, Trigger would in turn score a killing blow against the vessel, the resulting catastrophic detonation killing Torres and his crew.

He was described by an [[david_north|weapons analyst]]: "A devil incarnate." His bombastic delivery and insane ramblings ("Crisp white sheets!", "Salvation!", etc.) would result in him gaining a particularly memetic status among Ace Combat fans.

h4. See also
* "Matias Torres on the Ace Combat wiki":[https://acecombat.fandom.com/wiki/Matias_Torres]

title: regigigas
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #486 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Legendary Pokémon.
A gigantic white golem pokemon with yellow/ gold rings and attachments on its body, black symmetrical markings on its body, its 3 long simple fingers on each hand, moss growing on its shoulders and feet,6 spherical bulges on its sides (colored red, blue, and silver respectively.), and a pattern of 7 small dots on its 'face'. A pokemon of great strength and legendary stature, Regigigas is said to have effortlessly towed continents using nothing but ropes and is speculated to have created the pokemon Regirock, Regice, and Registeel using nothing but Clay/ rocks, arctic ice, and magma respectively. Regigigas is infamous however, for its unique ability, Slow Start, which halves its impressive attack and usable speed for 5 turns when it is sent out. While slow start was simply intended to balance Regigigas, it worked too well, and it is frequently called one of the worst legendary pokemon as a result, being featured in many comics and images poking fun at it.

It comes to life only when [[Regirock]], [[Regice]], and [[Registeel]] are gathered. Therefore, it requires the three to be in the player's party to awaken it within the Snowpoint Temple "[2]":[#dtext-external-links], Twist Mountain "[3]":[#dtext-external-links], or Island Cave "[4]":[#dtext-external-links], where it sleeps. In the first two locations, it will still be present if those Pokémon are absent, but it does not awaken and only seems to be a statue to the player.

Japanese Name: [[Regigigas]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Heatran]]
Next Pokémon: [[Giratina]]

h4#external-links. External Links

[1] Bulbagarden.net: "Regigigas":[http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Regigigas_(Pokémon)]
[2] Bulbagarden.net: "Snowpoint Temple":[http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Snowpoint_Temple] 
[3] Bulbagarden.net: "Twist Mountain":[http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Twist_Mountain]
[4] Bulbagarden.net: "Island Cave":[http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Island_Cave]

title: kogasa-san's_father
body: A being actually meant to represent [[Mizuki Hitoshi]]'s father within the context of his strip "Hang in There, Kogasa-san":/pools/2420.  Depicted as a dark gray [[karakasa obake]].  Like his son, he enjoys karaoke far more than he should, specializing in [i][[enka]][/i].  Sometimes referred to as "Papa-gasa" (父傘, [i]Chichi-gasa[/i]).

title: kogasa-san's_mother
body: A being actually meant to represent [[Mizuki Hitoshi]]'s mother within the context of his strip "Hang in There, Kogasa-san":/pools/2420.  Depicted as a (roughly) watermelon-red [[karakasa obake]].  As with most mothers of her generation, she's quite a cook.  Sometimes referred to as "Mama-gasa" (母傘, [i]Haha-gasa[/i]).

title: tang_wulin_(douluo_dalu)
body: The protagonist from Douluo Dalu 3, and 4. He is the son of the god king Poseidon, Tang San from Douluo Dalu. After the Golden Dragon King was defeated, and put it's god core into the baby Wulin for a chance for it's resurrection. His father then placed seals on the orb so that his son could try and assimilate the core, and become the next Golden Dragon King as well as sending him onto the Douluo Continent. He also has a deep romance with Gu Yue/Gu Yuena, but is constantly rejected since she is the lead of the near extinct Spirit Beast Race.

title: ugly_sonic
body:
The original design of [[Sonic the Hedgehog]] made for the [[sonic_the_hedgehog_(film)|2020 feature film]] that was met with such an overwhelmingly negative public reception that it prompted the studio to delay the film so that it could be re-edited with a newer design by artist [[Tyson Hesse]]. Particular attention has been called to the design's human-like teeth.

The name "Ugly Sonic" was given in the 2022 [i]Chip ‘n Dale: Rescue Rangers[/i] film, where the design was made into an actual character voiced by comedian Tim Robinson.
